REPORTS in Turkey said talks are going on between Sivasspor and representatives of Super Eagles midfielder Oghenekaro Etebo. Sivasspor manager has set his sights on landing the Nigeria midfielder, who featured on loan at Galatasaray last season. The Turkish Super Lig club, who finished outside the Top-4 this past campaign with Nigeria striker Olarenwaju Kayode, are considering a permanent or loan deal for the hard working Etebo. The former Warri Wolves star has a contract with England Championship side Stoke City till 2023. He has also played at Getafe in Spain on loan.